<size=30>Smooth "MoveTowards" Function</size>
Common function called to smoothly increase/decrease a parameter from it's current value to a target,

Text 1 = Parameter Name
Text 2 = Acceleration
Text 3 = Target value

Split our direction vector (Y rotation) into Sin and Cosine components)

SIN will be our forward/backward amount
COS will be our left/right amount

<size=20>Handle Movement Hotkeys</size>

We take the set Parameter name, create a "_+" and "_-" parameters that are either set to 0 or 1.

When 1, we ramp to our target speed (+ or -). when 0, we ramp down to 0.

When 0 and neither hotkey pressed, we stop calling our SmoothVal trigger

<size=30>Keyboard Control</size>
All the keyboard inputs to control the camera.

This these will only run when control mode is set to 1. There's a box for each XYZ of position and rotation. They all call SmoothVal to run, but will only do so when in motion.

Each has an Acceleration and speed scale.

Camera Drone Controller by Lunazera July 2025 (v1.0) - Control a camera using keyboard hotkeys or a gamepad. The main things you need to worry about are in the groups to the left and right of this message box. To use this, trigger SpawnCamera (or use the websocket to the left) and the camera should swap to the new view. Use your keyboard hotkey controls to move the camera around. If you want to use your gamepad, use the ControlMode toggle. There is also a Speed multipler parameter, CamMultiplier, you can use to speed up or slow down movement. On gamepad this is controlled with RB/LB. The idea with this was also to get position/rotation transforms for camera's that you could save and use for reference. This was made to control a camera, but you could control any custom object with this. Settings The right goup are the Main Settings, which are the custom object node, base speed, acceleration and deacceleration. Make sure it's set to spawn VNyanCam. The left node group has toggles and controls to manage the camera. Toggles - ControlMode (keyboard, gamepad, or nothing) - ControlToggle to quickly turn on and off controls - ToggleCamera to spawn camera & start controls at default location or destroy it. - Triggers to ResetPosition, ResetRotation, and ResetCamera (all settings) SaveCameraTransform trigger will save the XYZ position and rotation to the text parameter Controls Keyboard: SHIFT + WASD = move forward/backward/left/right SHIFT + QE = rotate left/right SHIFT + RF = move up/down CTRL + WS = rotate up/down CTRL + RF = twist left/right Gamepad: Left stick = move forward/backward/left/righ Right stick = rotate left/right, move up/down RB = Speed Up LB = Slow down LT/RT = rotate down/up DLeft = Reset all DUp = Reset position DDown = Reset Rotation X/Y = Twist

<size=20>Prepare Target Value</size>
1. Take Abs(value)
2. Scale with common Speed value

<size=20>Prepare Acceleration</size>
Scale with common Acc value

<size=20>Prepare Acceleration</size>
Prepare parameter name, using "name_+" and "name_-" parameters to get and convert a 1/0 boolean

<size=20>NOR Gate:</size>
Check if we are applying movement or not. If we let go of movement, we want to smoothly return to 0.
If both "name_+" and "name_-" = 0, then run true
If either are 1, then run false

<size=20>Returning to rest</size>
</size>First check if speed is above or below zero.
- If above, we next check what happens if we reduce by our acceleration. If it puts us below 0, clamp at 0. Otherwise save new value.
- If below, next check what happens if we increase by our acceleration. If it puts us above 0, clamp at 0, otherwise save new value

<size=20>Going Right</size>
</size>Check what happens if we increase our speed by acceleration.
- If that leaves us above our target value, then we clamp it there.
- If not, then check if target is positive value. If it is then save _speed + acceleration. If it's =< 0 (which means we're going reverse), then save _speed + deacceleration

<size=20>Going Left _-</size>
</size>Check what happens if we decrease our speed by acceleration.
- Compare against negative Target value. If Speed - Acceleration leaves us below our target value, then clamp at our negative speed.
- If not, then check if target is a positive value. If it is then save _speed - acceleration. If it's =< 0 (which means we're going reverse), then save _speed - deacceleration

<size=30>Settings</size>
Base movement speed and acceleration. These are scaled by a [CamMultiplier] to speed up or slow down with controls.

<size=30>Default Settings</size>
CameraControlMode = 1 -> set for Keyboard (make 2 if you want to default to gamepad)
CameraControlToggle = 1 -> set for controls to be active
